        S: '<p>The International Relations Office of the Royal University of Phnom Penh (RUPP) has a great honor to announce the batch 3 of the SHARE Scholarship for an exchange program to spend one academic semester or maximum six months in various ASEAN universities.</p>\n\n<p>For RUPP Students</p>\n\n<p>The RUPP students who wish to have exchange programs with SHARE participating universities should follow the steps below:</p>\n\n<p>1. Download the related forms (all forms can be filled in on the computer)<br />\n2. Surf relevant subjects from the host universities&#39; websites<br />\n3. Complete application for endorsement-RUPP<br />\n4. Apply for Letter of Endorsement for respective department and RUPP-IRO<br />\n5. Apply to Host University you wish to attend the exchange program<br />\n6. After receiving the Letter of Acceptance from the Host University, you have to apply for SHARE Scholarship<br />\n7. Commit to participate in two-week Pre-Departure Course<br />\n8. More related information refers: www.share-ASEAN.eu/scholarship</p>\n\n<p>Note:This scholarship is most applicable to students in years 2 and 3. Students in year 4 have to consult the respective department.</p>\n\n<p>For International Students</p>\n\n<p>The International students who wish to have exchange programs with RUPP under SHARE scheme (second batch) should follow the steps below:</p>\n\n<p>1. Submit endorsement letter from the home university<br />\n2. Complete application for acceptance of RUPP<br />\n3. Submit the scanned copy of the official transcript<br />\n4. Submit the evidence of English Language Proficiency<br />\n5. Contact RUPP-IRO or respective department you wish to study<br />\n6. Download the Application for Acceptance from RUPP admission</p>\n\n<p>The Exchange Program is under SHARE Scheme. Based on the SHARE Quota, we accept</p>\n\n<p>6 International students to DIS</p>\n\n<p>2 International students to English Department</p>\n\n<p>2 International students to DMC</p>\n',
