        S: '<h3>Bachelor Degree</h3><br /><br /><p>Prek Leap National College of Agriculture offers 4 years Bachelor Science in agricultural fields in the following specializations:</p><br /><br /><ol><li>Agricultural Science</li><li>Forestry Science</li><li>Fishery Science</li><li>Veterinary Medicine</li><li>Animal Science</li><li>Horticulture</li><li>Agricultural extension and Rural Development</li><li>Agricultural Economics</li><li>Food Processing</li><li>Nutrition and Health</li><li>Agricultural Engineering and Rural Construction</li><li>Cadastral and Land Management</li><li>Computer</li><li>English Language</li><li>Micro-Finance</li><li>Political Economy of Agriculture and Food</li></ol><br /><br /><p>The study program reflects the need for human resource development in agricultural sectors. The BSc study program consists of a number of compulsory subjects and some free elective subjects. In the final year, students are equipped to complete 6 months of research and write a thesis, then they have to defend their thesis in the final year to complete the course.</p><br /><br /><p><strong>The B.Sc PROGRAM IS SCHEDULED FOR 4 YEARS (127 CREDITS)</strong></p><br /><br /><ol><li>The Foundation Year study program will focus on general agricultural knowledge, general science, computer and English</li><li>Students will study specialization subjects which focus more on practical work and study tour</li><li>Students will complete 6 months of research and write a thesis, then they have to defend their thesis in the final year to complete the course.</li><li>Successful students will qualify for “Bachelor of Science Degree”</li></ol><br /><br /><p><strong>ENROLLMENT REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><br /><br /><ol><li><p>Candidates must have the high school certificate of the applicant year which has been selected by Ministry of Education, Youth and Sports (for scholarship students)</p></li><li><p>Candidates who have the high school certificate or associate degree or equivalence are eligible to enroll as paying students.</p></li></ol><br /><br /><h3>Associate Degree</h3><br /><br /><p>Prek Leap National College of Agriculture offers a 2 years associate degree program in the following specializations:</p><br /><br /><ol><li>Agronomy</li><li>Forestry</li><li>Fishery</li><li>Animal Health and Production</li><li>Horticulture</li><li>Agricultural extension and Rural Development</li><li>Agricultural Economics</li><li>Food Processing</li><li>Nutrition and Health</li><li>Agricultural Engineering and Rural Construction</li><li>Cadastral and Land Management</li><li>Computer</li><li>English Language</li><li>Micro-Finance</li><li>Political Economy of Agriculture and Food</li></ol><br /><br /><p><strong>GRADUATION REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><br /><br /><p>The AD study program consists of a number of compulsory subjects and some free elective subjects. In the final year, the student is equipped to write the final report and do the final examination to complete the course.</p><br /><br /><p>Students are required to have at least 60 credits (70 credits for those who do not have high school certificate).</p><br /><br /><p><strong>ENROLLMENT REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><br /><br /><ol><li><p>Candidates must have the high school certificate of the applicant year (for scholarship students)</p></li><li><p>Candidates who have a high school certificate from the previous year or failed high school certificate exam or equivalence are eligible to enroll as paying students.</p></li></ol>',
